"""v2-S03 sub-stage (e) — M3-ICP-locked: locked-scale rigid ICP on top
of the sz-pinned LP warm-start.

Design (distinct from C5/P1/P4/P6):
  - Stage A (LP + sz-pin) fixes all 7 DOF of the affine.  v2-S02 iter-7
    proves the sz pin matches GT to ±0.04 µm.  P1/P4/P6 each *re-fit*
    the full affine and may drift away from this prior.
  - Here: keep S, R^180 anchors fixed; iterate ONLY residual rigid
    (R_resid, t_resid) ∈ SE(3) on cz_init → hcr_gfp via robust NN
    matching.  Stops when |Δt| < 0.5 µm and |Δθ| < 0.2°, max 10 iters.
  - Output cell-cell pairs by NN in the final warped frame (1-NN per CZ;
    drop pairs with d > match_radius_um; rank by 1/(1 + d/σ_med)).

Goal: per-cell matching that respects the sz-pinned prior, as a
candidate that may beat C5 on subjects where C5's free-sz ensemble
drifts.

Outputs:
  bench_e_m3_icp_szpinned_results.csv
  bench_e_m3_icp_szpinned.log
"""
